items.term: A classical radical neck dissection (RND) involves excision of fibrofatty tissue and removal of lymph nodes from the mandible superiorly to the clavicle inferiorly (level I to level V), and in the unmodified procedure encompasses the sternocleidomastoid muscle, spinal accessory nerve and the internal jugular vein and may include additional structures such as the submandibular gland.
